<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 1:33PM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Potential for Patchy Slick Spots into this Evening...
As temperatures drop to below freezing behind a cold front through
sunset, any lingering light precipitation will be in the form of
patchy freezing drizzle. Patchy slick spots may develop on some
roadways, especially on bridges and overpasses, and on less
traveled or untreated roads. Leftover moisture on roads may
freeze into black ice during the evening due to temperatures
further cooling into the 20s. Leave extra time to reach your
destination through this evening and drive with caution.</description>
